[llm] Cleaned response: {"questions":[{"q":"In a recent biology class, students discussed the process of fertilization. They debated whether external factors can influence the success of fertilization in humans. Which statement best addresses their discussion?","o":["Fertilization can be influenced by factors such as hormonal balance and environmental conditions.","Fertilization is solely determined by genetic compatibility between sperm and egg.","Fertilization occurs independently of any external conditions.","Hormonal levels have no impact on the fertilization process."],"a":"A","d":"medium|hard","difficulty_weight":2,"question_type":"case_based","concept_pattern":"unique_snake_case_tag","explanation":"This question evaluates understanding of the factors influencing fertilization.","subject":"biology","public_subject":"biology","chapter":"Human Reproduction","topic":"Reproduction","concept":"Human Reproduction","concept_id":"biology::human_reproduction","pyq_anchor_id":"synthetic_cuet_structure_biology","anchor_tier":4,"passage_id":"optional_for_english_rc","passage_type":"optional_for_english_rc","passage_text":"optional_for_english_rc"},{"q":"During a health class, students learned about the importance of reproductive health. One student argued that reproductive health only involves physical aspects, while another emphasized psychological well-being as well. Which perspective is more accurate?","o":["Reproductive health encompasses both physical and psychological aspects, making it a holistic concept.","Reproductive health is primarily focused on physical health and reproductive functions only.","Psychological aspects are secondary to physical conditions in reproductive health.","Reproductive health is mainly concerned with social issues rather than individual well-being."],"a":"A","d":"medium|hard","difficulty_weight":2,"question_type":"application_based","concept_pattern":"unique_snake_case_tag","explanation":"This question tests the application of reproductive health concepts in a real-world context.","subject":"biology","public_subject":"biology","chapter":"Human Reproduction","topic":"Reproduction","concept":"Human Reproduction","concept_id":"biology::human_reproduction","pyq_anchor_id":"synthetic_cuet_structure_biology","anchor_tier":4,"passage_id":"optional_for_english_rc","passage_type":"optional_for_english_rc","passage_text":"optional_for_english_rc"},{"q":"Comparing sexual reproduction and asexual reproduction, which statement correctly highlights their differences in human contexts?","o":["Sexual reproduction involves genetic mixing, while asexual reproduction results in identical offspring.","Asexual reproduction allows for genetic variation, whereas sexual reproduction does not.","Both processes involve the same mechanisms for producing offspring in humans.","Sexual reproduction does not require gametes, unlike asexual reproduction."],"a":"A","d":"medium|hard","difficulty_weight":2,"question_type":"comparison_based","concept_pattern":"unique_snake_case_tag","explanation":"This question assesses the understanding of reproductive methods in humans.","subject":"biology","public_subject":"biology","chapter":"Human Reproduction","topic":"Reproduction","concept":"Human Reproduction","concept_id":"biology::human_reproduction","pyq_anchor_id":"synthetic_cuet_structure_biology","anchor_tier":4,"passage_id":"optional_for_english_rc","passage_type":"optional_for_english_rc","passage_text":"optional_for_english_rc"},{"q":"Statement I: The menstrual cycle is regulated by hormones including estrogen and progesterone. Statement II: Hormonal fluctuations have no effect on mood or behavior during the menstrual cycle. Which statements are correct?","o":["Statement I is correct; Statement II is incorrect.","Both statements are correct, as hormones do not affect mood.","Statement I is incorrect; Statement II is correct.","Both statements are incorrect regarding hormonal influence."],"a":"A","d":"medium|hard","difficulty_weight":2,"question_type":"statement_based","concept_pattern":"unique_snake_case_tag","explanation":"This question evaluates comprehension of hormonal roles in the menstrual cycle.","subject":"biology","public_subject":"biology","chapter":"Human Reproduction","topic":"Reproduction","concept":"Human Reproduction","concept_id":"biology::human_reproduction","pyq_anchor_id":"synthetic_cuet_structure_biology","anchor_tier":4,"passage_id":"optional_for_english_rc","passage_type":"optional_for_english_rc","passage_text":"optional_for_english_rc"},{"q":"Assertion: Male and female reproductive systems function independently without interaction. Reason: The male reproductive system produces sperm without any influence from the female system. Evaluate the validity of the assertion and reason provided.","o":["Both assertion and reason are false, as interaction exists between systems during reproduction.","The assertion is true but the reason is false; both systems interact during reproduction.","The assertion is false but the reason is true; sperm production involves female influence.","Both assertion and reason are true; they do not affect each other."],"a":"A","d":"medium|hard","difficulty_weight":2,"question_type":"assertion_reason","concept_pattern":"unique_snake_case_tag","explanation":"This question assesses understanding of reproductive system interactions.","subject":"biology","public_subject":"biology","chapter":"Human Reproduction","topic":"Reproduction","concept":"Human Reproduction","concept_id":"biology::human_reproduction","pyq_anchor_id":"synthetic_cuet_structure_biology","anchor_tier":4,"passage_id":"optional_for_english_rc","passage_type":"optional_for_english_rc","passage_text":"optional_for_english_rc"}]}
